308. hinc, i.e. ex capris. Goats commonly bear twins, some- times triplets, and supply milk enough for rearing their young and for home consumption as well.

309, 310. quam magis . . . (tam) magiS, instead of the usual quo . . . eo. The literal sense is ‘the more milk you take at the first milking,the greater will be the yield at the next ' ; i. e. however much you have already taken, there will be plenty more to come. For the poetical epithet laeta, here==‘ copious,‘ ‘rich,' see note on 1. 1.
